place.name: WEST RUDHAM
place.gazetteerText: RUDHAM (West), a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 7 miles W by S of Fakenham r. station. Post-town, East Rudham, under Brandon. Acres, 2, 835. Real property, £4, 546. Pop., 487. Houses, 112. The living is a vicarage, annexed to East Rudham. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
